locationName: Tinker Logistics Center
facilityType: Air Logistics Complex - DLA Distribution Center
notes: Oklahoma City Air Logistics Complex - One of three major Air Force logistics complexes. Provides depot maintenance and supply chain management.

locationName: Ogden Logistics Complex
facilityType: Air Logistics Complex - DLA Distribution Hill
notes: Ogden Air Logistics Complex - Major Air Force logistics hub supporting multiple weapon systems and providing depot-level maintenance.

locationName: Warner Robins Logistics Complex
notes: Warner Robins Air Logistics Complex - Named after the 'father of logistics' in the Air Force. Largest industrial complex in Georgia.

locationName: Wright-Patterson Logistics Center
notes: Home to Air Force Materiel Command. Major research, development, and logistics hub for Air Force operations.

locationName: Travis Logistics Center
notes: 60th Logistics Readiness Squadron - Largest Aircraft Parts Store in Air Mobility Command. Strategic airlift hub for Pacific operations.

locationName: Dover Logistics Center
notes: 436th Logistics Readiness Squadron - East Coast strategic airlift hub. Critical logistics support for Atlantic operations.

locationName: McChord Logistics Center
notes: Joint Army-Air Force installation. 62nd Airlift Wing provides worldwide strategic airlift. Logistics Gate operates 24/7.

locationName: Scott Logistics Center
notes: 375th Logistics Readiness Squadron - Home to Air Mobility Command headquarters. Central logistics hub for AMC operations.

locationName: Lackland Logistics Center
notes: Part of Joint Base San Antonio. Primary location for Air Force basic training and major logistics operations in Southwest.

locationName: Charleston Logistics Center
notes: 628th Logistics Readiness Squadron - Joint Air Force and Navy installation. Provides rapid global mobility support with over $500M in supplies and equipment.

locationName: Nellis Combat Operations
notes: Home of the Fighter Pilot. 57th Wing hosts advanced combat training including Red Flag exercises. Approximately 11,000 military personnel.

locationName: Edwards Test Center
notes: Air Force Test Center and Test Pilot School. Primary center for aerospace research, development, and testing. Located 100 miles northeast of Los Angeles.

locationName: Offutt Strategic Command
notes: Headquarters of U.S. Strategic Command (USSTRATCOM). Home to 55th Wing and 557th Weather Wing. Located south of Omaha.

locationName: Minot Bomber Wing
notes: 5th Bomb Wing with B-52H Stratofortress. Also home to 91st Missile Wing. One of two remaining B-52 bases in USAF.

locationName: Barksdale Bomber Operations
notes: 2nd Bomb Wing - Oldest bomb wing in USAF. Equipped with approximately 44 B-52H Stratofortress bombers.

locationName: Ellsworth Bomber Wing
notes: 28th Bomb Wing with B-1B Lancer. One of two B-1B wings in USAF. Located 10 miles northeast of Rapid City.

locationName: Luke Fighter Training
notes: 56th Fighter Wing - Largest fighter wing in USAF. Primary F-16 and F-35 training base. Located west of Phoenix.

locationName: Dyess Bomber Wing
notes: 7th Bomb Wing with B-1B Lancer. One of two B-1B strategic bomber wings in USAF. Located southwest of Abilene.

locationName: Seymour Johnson Fighter Wing
notes: 4th Fighter Wing. Responsible for training all F-15E Strike Eagle aircrews for the Air Force. Located in eastern North Carolina.

locationName: Peterson Space Operations
notes: Space Force installation. Shares runways with Colorado Springs Airport. Critical space operations and defense missions.

locationName: Buckley Space Operations
notes: Space Force base supporting space-based missile warning, space surveillance, and satellite operations. Located in Aurora metro area.

locationName: Kirtland Research Center
notes: Major research and development facility. Adjacent to Albuquerque International Sunport. Multiple research laboratories and test facilities.

locationName: Langley Fighter Operations
facilityType: Fighter Wing - Air Combat Command HQ
notes: Headquarters of Air Combat Command. 1st Fighter Wing with F-22 Raptors. Joint Army-Air Force installation in Hampton Roads area.

locationName: Andrews Presidential Airlift
notes: Home of Air Force One. 316th Wing provides airlift for President, Vice President, and senior government officials. Located in Prince George's County.

locationName: Hurlburt Special Operations
notes: Air Force Special Operations Command headquarters. 1st Special Operations Wing. Located in Florida Panhandle west of Mary Esther.
